org.franca.core.franca

Interface FCompoundType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, FModelElement, FType, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FStructType, FUnionType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FCompoundTypeImpl, FStructTypeImpl, FUnionTypeImpl

    public interface FCompoundType
extends FType
    A representation of the model object 'FCompound Type'. This class represents all kinds of compound types in Franca, i.e., struct and union types. A compound type has a list of fields; each field is itself specified by its type. Thus, nested compounds can be created. The ordering of fields in the compound is relevant. E.g., serialization code generated from a Franca interface must take into account the order of the fields.

    The following features are supported:

    • Elements

    See Also:
    FrancaPackage.getFCompoundType()
